<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                    <head>No. 146.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 6,
                            1887</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Directs Mr. Denby to express to the Chinese Government the surprise and
                        regret with which the United States learn of obstruction being placed by
                        Chinese officials in the way of Corea’s diplomatic representation in the
                        United States as stipulated in existing treaty.</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>